places.name: Queen Beatrix International Airport
places.perex: Queen Beatrix International Airport, is an international airport located in Oranjestad, Aruba.

places.name: Eagle Beach
places.perex: Eagle Beach is a beach and neighborhood of Oranjestad, Aruba. The neighborhood is famous for its many low-rise resorts and wide public beach.

places.name: Natural Pool
places.perex: Finding this pool is a real experience as the way lacks almost any signposting. Yet definitely worth it!

places.name: Butterfly Farm
places.perex: Visit to this butterfly farm is something you are not likely to forget. Butterflies of various shapes and colours are so fascinating!

places.name: California Lighthouse
places.perex: Landmark of Aruba. Climb it to enjoy the spectacular views of the island.

places.name: Baby Beach
places.perex: Beach perfect for families with even the small kids - it is naturally protected from waves and the water is very shallow.

places.name: Casibari Rock
places.perex: These huge boulders are a perfect vantage point for overlooking the island. If you're lucky, you will see Venezuela from here.

places.name: Arashi Beach
places.perex: This beach is simply amazing - a perfect snorkelling location and the water sport lovers have their share of enjoyment here too.

places.name: Bushiribana
places.perex: Bushiribana and Balashi are the sites of two former gold smelters on the Caribbean island of Aruba.

places.name: Ayo Rock Formation
places.perex: Ayo Rock Formations are monolithic rock boulders located on the island of Aruba in the Caribbean.

places.name: Hooiberg
places.perex: Hooiberg is a 165 m high volcanic formation on the island of Aruba. It is located almost in the center of the island and can be seen from…

places.name: Barefoot Restaurant
places.perex: A beachside restaurant and bar serving amazing seafood and mixed drinks. A great dining experience.

places.name: Mount Jamanota
places.perex: Mount Jamanota is the highest point on the island of Aruba and is visible from the entire island.

places.name: Guadirkiri Caves
places.perex: A typical cave with several rock formations and narrow corridors. Beautiful place off the beaten path.

places.name: The Antilla
places.perex: SS Antilla was a Hamburg America Line cargo ship that was launched in 1939 and scuttled in 1940.

places.name: The Flying Fishbone
places.perex: Enjoy your delicious meal in the vicinity of the sea - this is simply an amazing open-air restaurant.

places.name: Malmok Beach
places.perex: Exceptionally translucent water poses the best snorkelling and diving opportunities on the island!

places.name: Wilhelmina Park
places.perex: Small but lovely waterfront park dedicated to the Dutch Queen is a nice place to wander around and watch the sunset.

places.name: Rodgers Beach
places.perex: Come to this beach to watch the spectacular sunset or just to swim - the waters are very calm and shallow, too.

places.name: Salt and Pepper
places.perex: Very popular breakfast and brunch spot that does attract locals as well. Come here to start your day in style!

places.name: Druif Beach
places.perex: Lined with resort, this beach is favourite spot for the tourist crowd. Perfect for families with kids as well as those who like to party.

places.name: Olde Molen
places.perex: This mill is one of the few last remnants of Dutch colonial heritage. Constructed in 19th century in the Netherlands and then moved to Aruba.

places.name: Huliba Cave
places.perex: Also being called "tunnel of love" for its beautiful heart-shaped entrance. Don't forget to take flashlight with you.

places.name: Philip's Animal Garden
places.perex: Small zoo that holds a portion of rescue animals - an unique opportunity to see the local wildlife.

places.name: Fontein Cave
places.perex: This tiny cave has beautiful drawings made by the indigenous Arawak people - a fascinating display of the local culture.

places.name: Archaeological Museum
places.perex: A must for history buffs! This museum presents an amazing collection of archaeological finds and memorabilia.

places.name: Boca Grandi
places.perex: White, almost powder-like sand with rough sea is sought after mostly by windsurfers and surfers.

places.name: Santa Ana Chapel
places.perex: Roman Catholic church was rebuilt two times and still serves as an important religious meeting point.
